{"key":"processedPost-8669584","value":{"id":8669584,"first":8668802,"last":8670863,"when":1216786382,"utime":"07/23/08 07:13 AM","content":"You should NEVER incubate anything, but large substrates such as straw logs and laundry baskets can produce up to 20F extra heat on their own.&nbsp; If you're 'incubating' at 80F, your substrate can easily reach 100F, killing the mycelium and leaving the straw open for competitor fungi.&nbsp; Allow straw logs and laundry baskets to colonize in room temperature or slightly below.<br /><br />In addition, silly incubators tend to cut off the gas exchange, which further increases chances of contamination.&nbsp; <br />RR","title":"Re: question about straw"}}